[1] Australia (Queensland) ex New Zealand
Date: Tue 8 Oct 2019
Source: Central Telegraph [abridged, edited]
https://www.centraltelegraph.com.au/news/qld-records-sixth-measles-case-in-a-fortnight/3849264/


Another measles case has flown into the Gold Coast from New Zealand, which is experiencing an epidemic of the highly contagious virus.

The case is the 3rd reported on the Gold Coast and the 6th measles case diagnosed in Queensland in the past fortnight. It takes the number of cases in Queensland so far this year to 31, more than double the 14 recorded for the whole of 2018.

The traveller was exposed to measles while visiting New Zealand, which has recorded more than 1600 cases this year [2019].

[Byline: Janelle Miles]

