[5] Massachusetts (Boston)
Date: Wed 9 Oct 2019
Source: CBS Local [abridged, edited]
https://boston.cbslocal.com/2019/10/09/boston-measles-case-exposure-locations/


A Boston resident has the city's 1st confirmed case of the measles since 2013. The Public Health Commission announced Wednesday [9 Oct 2019] that others may have been exposed at a number of locations in the South End, Fenway, and Back Bay neighborhoods.

Doctors diagnosed the case on Sunday [6 Oct 2019]. Health officials released [a list] of locations in Boston and times where the person could have exposed others [see URL above for list. - Mod.LK].

