[Also see https://www.apnews.com/f45e17d506f842f3ad10f3080d57ed48. More than 4000 people have died in Congo this year [2019] in the world's largest measles outbreak, the UN's children's agency said Wednesday [9 Oct 2019]. Since January [2019], more than 200 000 cases of measles have been reported across Congo, UNICEF said. More than 140 000 involve children under 5, who also make up nearly 90% of deaths. UNICEF said health workers were rushing additional medical kits to help care for more than 110 000 people infected with the measles, a highly contagious and potentially deadly virus. More than 1.4 million children have been vaccinated this year [2019]. - Mod.LK]

